    <p>The 1980s is when beef ruled cinema.</p>
    <p>The the­atre of mas­culin­ity had no big­ger stage than with the first Preda­tor movie in 1987.</p>
    <p>The alien-hunt ac­tion-thriller opens with Arnold Sch­warzeneg­ger and Carl Weath­ers arm-wrestling, with ador­ing close-ups of their glis­ten­ing arms.</p>
    <p>Ac­com­pany your view­ing with a drink­ing game: Take a shot when­ever a quotable line in the movie is ut­tered, like “Get to the choppa!”, “I ain’t got time to bleed” or “If it bleeds, we can kill it”.</p>
